MINNA – A Niger State governorship aspirant on the platform of All Progressives Congress (APC) and Publisher of BluePrints Newspapers, Alhaji Mohammed Idris Malagi, has donated grains and oil worth N27 million to Internal Displaced Persons (IDPs) and his party members. The aspirants’ donation is however received not without mixed feelings as citizens raise concerns over the recklessness of the drivers that delivered the consignments, advising him to engage more capable hands that will not cause destruction to properties. Presenting the food items to the state APC executives, Malagi who was represented by the Co-ordinating Secretary of, Malagi 2023 Gubernatorial Organization, Bala Marka, said the food items include 1, 750 bags of rice and maize and as well as 50 king size oil of 25 litres and N1 million cash to transport the items to beneficiaries. The items, according to Malagi, are for the APC executives at the ward, zonal and state levels. He added that the gesture is to support party members in cushioning the effects of the socio-economic hardship as they continue with Ramadan fast. Also at the Housing Corporation, Marka handed over assorted food items to the Niger state government through the Director General, Niger State Emergency Management Agency (NSEMA), Alhaji Ibrahim Inga for onward distribution to the IDPs. Bala Marka gave a breakdown of the food items donated to the IDPs to ameliorate their sufferings including; 450 bags of rice, maize and millet 150 each and 50 jerry cans of 25 litres of vegetable oil. In their respective responses, state APC Chairman, Alhaji Haliru Zakari Jikantoro and Ibrahim Inga thanked the governorship aspirant for the show of concern for the wellbeing of party members and the IDPs.